HEADWORD: Mazer
<hw>Maz"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>maser</ets>,
akin to OD. <ets>maser</ets> an excrescence on a maple tree, OHG.
<ets>masar</ets>, G. <ets>maser</ets> spot, Icel. <ets>m⟦oum⟧surr</ets>
maple.]</ety> <def>A large drinking bowl; -- originally made of
maple.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their brimful <qex>mazers</qex> to the feasting bring.</q>
<rj><qau>Drayton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

